<p>
<A HREF="http://mips.gsf.de/proj/gabi/">
GABI-Info
</A> is the bioinformatics resource center within GABI which 
develops and supplies bioinformatics tools. It serves the 
specific needs of the GABI projects in terms of data 
analysis. A metabolic pathway database will be developed 
which will link genomic and metabolic information. 
<A HREF="http://mips.gsf.de/proj/gabi/news/bioinformatics.html">
Software tools
</A> developed for researchers are the BioRS, HarvESTer and 
SPUTNIK. BioRS is a powerful and fast retrieval system 
offering state of the art integration of heterogeneous 
databanks with other proprietary databases. HarvESTer is a 
sophisticated, high throughput clustering and assembly tool 
with a series of flexible modules that address specific 
issues of EST (Expressed Sequence Tag) data processing. 
SPUTNIK is a database schema designed to apply the principles 
of plant-intergenomic analysis to the large number of plant 
species that are currently lacking significant genomic 
sequence, but which contain a hidden wealth of pertinent 
sequence in the form of ESTs. The "genomeless genomic" 
analyses are prepared by assembling a non-redundant set of 
overlapping sequences (clusters), deriving peptide-sequences 
and performing exhaustive genome-scale analyses on this 
prepared population. The SPUTNIK project aims to provide 
plant-researchers worldwide with an interactive in-depth 
resource covering numerous aspects of contemporary plant-
genomics including functional assignment, structural 
description and detailed marker analysis.
